20/07/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- A member of the Greek November 17 terrorist group was paroled on Wednesday (19 July) after serving half of his eight-year sentence. Nikos Papanastasiou was one of the founding members of the organisation, which is blamed for the murders of 23 people between 1975 and 2000. He was convicted in 2002. Fifteen members of the same group are currently appealing sentences ranging from eight years to life. (AP - 19/07/06) 
